definitions.definition: ( historical ) Until 1995, a province of central Belgium ; since divided into Flemish Brabant , Brussels-Capital Region and Walloon Brabant .
Duchy of Brabant; a historical region, roughly comprising the area of modern Flemish and Walloon Brabant, Brussels, the Belgian province of Antwerp , and the Dutch province of North Brabant .

definitions.definition: A draft horse of a strong, heavy breed originating from the Brabant region of modern Belgium .
